A set of criteria was selected based on literature review and through the discussion with some experts in the area. The selected criteria include economic, technical, environmental and social criteria, and these criteria are as follows: Social acceptance (mentioned as C1 in the calculations), Possibilities of new job positions (
C 2
), Investment cost (C3), Production of solid outcast (C4), Level of possible environmental repercussions (C5), Adaptability in the local conditions (C6), and Air emissions (C7). The first, second, and sixth criteria are positive criteria, the rest are negative criteria. Criteria weights will first be calculated using the FUCOM method. The steps will be explained in some detail.
